--SUG: let's use the following shorthands:
--  cdx - a column index aka COLUMNS[cdx]               -- (program-friendly) [cdx=coldrag[ddx]]        \ treat atom(coldrag) as    \  and/or
--  ddx - a dragged index aka COLUMNS[coldrag[ddx]]     -- (display-friendly) [ddx=find(cdx,coldrag)]   / tagset(length(COLUMNS))   / cdx==ddx
--  rdx - a row index aka DATA[rdx]                     -- (program-friendly) [rdx=tags[sdx]]   \  These are nowhere    \   famous
--  sdx - a sorted index aka DATA[tags[sdx]]            -- (display-friendly) [sdx=itag[rdx]]   / near as troublesome   / last words
-- New strategy: whenever we pass a line, indicate as well whether it is an rdx or sdx, but let's get unsorted selection working first...
-- By program-friendly I mean an application can use a gTable without caring whether it is sorted/reordered.
-- By display-friendly I mean that's where this program displays things and where clicks/hover/etc happen.
--local enum TG_TABLE_CDX, TG_TABLE_DDX, TG_TABLE_RDX, TG_TABLE_SDX
